Lt. Cmdr. Amanda Higgins 30-Aug-20 02:11 AM
Amanda yawned a bit as she walked into her now repaired quarters. She looked around and smiled as she saw a larger bed and all of her things neatly placed around the room. She busied herself with putting new hay in Tony's hutch, a two story large house shaped cage with no actual cage parts. It was kept open at all time so Tony could come and go as he pleased. Tony hopped down to chew a bit on his new carrot toy and settled down for the evening. Amanda yawned again and took off her uniform, changing into her sleep clothes before heading to the replicator. She decided to have one of her guilty pleasures, "computer, one slice of New York style pizza with olives." She ate in relative silence, reviewing some of the repairs from the day and sending out instructions to her teams. An unopened message beeped at her and she groaned as she opened it. A letter from her parents flashed on the screen, mostly pleasantries and the indication that they both had some leave and would loooove to see her. Her nose crinkled and she sighed as she messaged back her affirmative that she would visit soon. After recycling her plate and taking a quick shower, she settled into bed. Her eyes moved towards the regeneration module in the corner of the room, she turned away from it and closed her eyes.
